annotationA: Malic Enzyme (Men) is a dehydrogenase that catalyzes the oxidation of malate to pyruvate, with the concomitant reduction of NADP(+) to NADPH. Men functions, along with Idh, Zw, and Pgd, in a small network of NADP reducing enzymes
annotationB: Malate dehydrogenase 2 is one of the enzymes in the tricarboxylic acid cycle in mitochondria; Belongs to the LDH/MDH superfamily
